Patch Set 5:

I've addressed Alexander Tivelkov comments. I want to emphasize that asserts in _compare_json_file_with_db method has different ordering of arguments depends on calling context. So for example in _assert_database_loaded_from_json_file method expected value is part of json file and observed value is appropriate db record but in _assert_export_metadefs method expected value is db record and observed is part of json file.

What I want to add is that for the last patchset from this review :https://review.openstack.org/#/c/120432/ coverage of this functional tests should be increased (it should cover calling glance-manage db_load_metadefs twice for example)

The way you do it is: ask DB for all the data, build dictionary and then iterate through it comparing with json file.

Why don't you just make the dictionary the same way that db_export_metadefs does and just compare whole dicts without iterating through them?
